  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00006_A2018-24_1542613153379&sectionId=30949&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00006_A2018-24_1542613153379
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the National Commission for`
  line `Backward Classes (Repeal) Act, 2018.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 15th August, 2018, vide notification No. S.O. 3988(E), dated 14th August, 2018, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec.`
  line `3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (30950)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00006_A2018-24_1542613153379&sectionId=30950&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00006_A2018-24_1542613153379
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Commission for Backward Classes Act, 1993 (27 of`
  line `1993) is hereby repealed and the National Commission for Backward Classes constituted under subsection (1) of section 3 of the said Act shall stand dissolved.`
  line
  line `(2) The repeal of the National Commission for Backward Classes Act, 1993 (27 of 1993) shall,`
  line `however, not affect,—`
  line
  line `(i) the previous operation of the Act so repealed or anything duly done or suffered thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any right, privilege, obligation or liability acquired, accrued or incurred under the Act so repealed;`
  line or
  line
  line `(iii) any penalty, confiscation or punishment incurred in respect of any contravention under the Act so`
  line `repealed; or`
  line
  line `(iv) any proceeding or remedy in respect of any such right, privilege, obligation, liability, penalty,`
  line `confiscation or punishment as aforesaid, and any such proceeding or remedy may be instituted, continued or`
  line `enforced, and any such penalty, confiscation or punishment may be imposed or made as if that Act had not`
  line `been repealed.`
  line
  line `(3) The mention of the particular matters referred to in sub-section (2) shall not be held to prejudice or`
  line `affect the general application of section 6 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897) with regard to the`
  line `effect of repeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
